46 void c_typecheck_baset::typecheck_expr(exprt &expr)
47 {
48  if(expr.id()==ID_already_typechecked)
49  {
50  expr.swap(to_already_typechecked_expr(expr).get_expr());
51  return;
52  }
53 
54  // first do sub-nodes
55  typecheck_expr_operands(expr);
56 
57  // now do case-split
58  typecheck_expr_main(expr);
59 }

61 void c_typecheck_baset::add_rounding_mode(exprt &expr)
62 {
63  for(auto &op : expr.operands())
64  add_rounding_mode(op);
65 
66  if(expr.id()==ID_div ||
67  expr.id()==ID_mult ||
68  expr.id()==ID_plus ||
69  expr.id()==ID_minus)
70  {
71  if(expr.type().id()==ID_floatbv &&
72  expr.operands().size()==2)
73  {
74  // The rounding mode to be used at compile time is non-obvious.
75  // We'll simply use round to even (0), which is suggested
76  // by Sec. F.7.2 Translation, ISO-9899:1999.
77  expr.operands().resize(3);
78 
79  if(expr.id()==ID_div)
80  expr.id(ID_floatbv_div);
81  else if(expr.id()==ID_mult)
82  expr.id(ID_floatbv_mult);
83  else if(expr.id()==ID_plus)
84  expr.id(ID_floatbv_plus);
85  else if(expr.id()==ID_minus)
86  expr.id(ID_floatbv_minus);
87  else
88  UNREACHABLE;
89 
90  to_ieee_float_op_expr(expr).rounding_mode() =
91  from_integer(0, unsigned_int_type());
92  }
93  }
94 }

96 bool c_typecheck_baset::gcc_types_compatible_p(
97  const typet &type1,
98  const typet &type2)
99 {
100  // read
101  // http://gcc.gnu.org/onlinedocs/gcc-3.3.6/gcc/Other-Builtins.html
102 
103  // check qualifiers first
104  if(c_qualifierst(type1)!=c_qualifierst(type2))
105  return false;
106 
107  if(type1.id()==ID_c_enum_tag)
108  return gcc_types_compatible_p(follow_tag(to_c_enum_tag_type(type1)), type2);
109  else if(type2.id()==ID_c_enum_tag)
110  return gcc_types_compatible_p(type1, follow_tag(to_c_enum_tag_type(type2)));
111 
112  if(type1.id()==ID_c_enum)
113  {
114  if(type2.id()==ID_c_enum) // both are enums
115  return type1==type2; // compares the tag
116  else if(type2 == to_c_enum_type(type1).underlying_type())
117  return true;
118  }
119  else if(type2.id()==ID_c_enum)
120  {
121  if(type1 == to_c_enum_type(type2).underlying_type())
122  return true;
123  }
124  else if(type1.id()==ID_pointer &&
125  type2.id()==ID_pointer)
126  {
127  return gcc_types_compatible_p(
128  to_pointer_type(type1).base_type(), to_pointer_type(type2).base_type());
129  }
130  else if(type1.id()==ID_array &&
131  type2.id()==ID_array)
132  {
133  return gcc_types_compatible_p(
134  to_array_type(type1).element_type(),
135  to_array_type(type2).element_type()); // ignore size
136  }
137  else if(type1.id()==ID_code &&
138  type2.id()==ID_code)
139  {
140  const code_typet &c_type1=to_code_type(type1);
141  const code_typet &c_type2=to_code_type(type2);
142 
143  if(!gcc_types_compatible_p(
144  c_type1.return_type(),
145  c_type2.return_type()))
146  return false;
147 
148  if(c_type1.parameters().size()!=c_type2.parameters().size())
149  return false;
150 
151  for(std::size_t i=0; i<c_type1.parameters().size(); i++)
152  if(!gcc_types_compatible_p(
153  c_type1.parameters()[i].type(),
154  c_type2.parameters()[i].type()))
155  return false;
156 
157  return true;
158  }
159  else
160  {
161  if(type1==type2)
162  {
163  // Need to distinguish e.g. long int from int or
164  // long long int from long int.
165  // The rules appear to match those of C++.
166 
167  if(type1.get(ID_C_c_type)==type2.get(ID_C_c_type))
168  return true;
169  }
170  }
171 
172  return false;
173 }

175 void c_typecheck_baset::typecheck_expr_main(exprt &expr)
176 {
177  if(expr.id()==ID_side_effect)
178  typecheck_expr_side_effect(to_side_effect_expr(expr));
179  else if(expr.is_constant())
180  typecheck_expr_constant(expr);
181  else if(expr.id()==ID_infinity)
182  {
183  // ignore
184  }
185  else if(expr.id()==ID_symbol)
186  typecheck_expr_symbol(expr);
187  else if(expr.id()==ID_unary_plus ||
188  expr.id()==ID_unary_minus ||
189  expr.id()==ID_bitnot)
190  typecheck_expr_unary_arithmetic(expr);
191  else if(expr.id()==ID_not)
192  typecheck_expr_unary_boolean(expr);
193  else if(
194  expr.id() == ID_and || expr.id() == ID_or || expr.id() == ID_implies ||
195  expr.id() == ID_xor)
196  typecheck_expr_binary_boolean(expr);
197  else if(expr.id()==ID_address_of)
198  typecheck_expr_address_of(expr);
199  else if(expr.id()==ID_dereference)
200  typecheck_expr_dereference(expr);
201  else if(expr.id()==ID_member)
202  typecheck_expr_member(expr);
203  else if(expr.id()==ID_ptrmember)
204  typecheck_expr_ptrmember(expr);
205  else if(expr.id()==ID_equal ||
206  expr.id()==ID_notequal ||
207  expr.id()==ID_lt ||
208  expr.id()==ID_le ||
209  expr.id()==ID_gt ||
210  expr.id()==ID_ge)
211  typecheck_expr_rel(to_binary_relation_expr(expr));
212  else if(expr.id()==ID_index)
213  typecheck_expr_index(expr);
214  else if(expr.id()==ID_typecast)
215  typecheck_expr_typecast(expr);
216  else if(expr.id()==ID_sizeof)
217  typecheck_expr_sizeof(expr);
218  else if(expr.id()==ID_alignof)
219  typecheck_expr_alignof(expr);
220  else if(
221  expr.id() == ID_plus || expr.id() == ID_minus || expr.id() == ID_mult ||
222  expr.id() == ID_div || expr.id() == ID_mod || expr.id() == ID_bitand ||
223  expr.id() == ID_bitxor || expr.id() == ID_bitor || expr.id() == ID_bitnand)
224  {
225  typecheck_expr_binary_arithmetic(expr);
226  }
227  else if(expr.id()==ID_shl || expr.id()==ID_shr)
228  typecheck_expr_shifts(to_shift_expr(expr));
229  else if(expr.id()==ID_comma)
230  typecheck_expr_comma(expr);
231  else if(expr.id()==ID_if)
232  typecheck_expr_trinary(to_if_expr(expr));
233  else if(expr.id()==ID_code)
234  {
235  error().source_location = expr.source_location();
236  error() << "typecheck_expr_main got code: " << expr.pretty() << eom;
237  throw 0;
238  }
239  else if(expr.id()==ID_gcc_builtin_va_arg)
240  typecheck_expr_builtin_va_arg(expr);
241  else if(expr.id()==ID_cw_va_arg_typeof)
242  typecheck_expr_cw_va_arg_typeof(expr);
243  else if(expr.id()==ID_gcc_builtin_types_compatible_p)
244  {
245  expr.type()=bool_typet();
246  auto &subtypes =
247  (static_cast<type_with_subtypest &>(expr.add(ID_type_arg))).subtypes();
248  PRECONDITION(subtypes.size() == 2);
249  typecheck_type(subtypes[0]);
250  typecheck_type(subtypes[1]);
251  source_locationt source_location=expr.source_location();
252 
253  // ignores top-level qualifiers
254  subtypes[0].remove(ID_C_constant);
255  subtypes[0].remove(ID_C_volatile);
256  subtypes[0].remove(ID_C_restricted);
257  subtypes[1].remove(ID_C_constant);
258  subtypes[1].remove(ID_C_volatile);
259  subtypes[1].remove(ID_C_restricted);
260 
261  expr = make_boolean_expr(gcc_types_compatible_p(subtypes[0], subtypes[1]));
262  expr.add_source_location()=source_location;
263  }
264  else if(expr.id()==ID_clang_builtin_convertvector)
265  {
266  // This has one operand and a type, and acts like a typecast
267  DATA_INVARIANT(expr.operands().size()==1, "clang_builtin_convertvector has one operand");
268  typecheck_type(expr.type());
269  typecast_exprt tmp(to_unary_expr(expr).op(), expr.type());
270  tmp.add_source_location()=expr.source_location();
271  expr.swap(tmp);
272  }
273  else if(expr.id()==ID_builtin_offsetof)
274  typecheck_expr_builtin_offsetof(expr);
275  else if(expr.id()==ID_string_constant)
276  {
277  // already fine -- mark as lvalue
278  expr.set(ID_C_lvalue, true);
279  }
280  else if(expr.id()==ID_arguments)
281  {
282  // already fine
283  }
284  else if(expr.id()==ID_designated_initializer)
285  {
286  exprt &designator=static_cast<exprt &>(expr.add(ID_designator));
287 
288  Forall_operands(it, designator)
289  {
290  if(it->id()==ID_index)
291  typecheck_expr(to_unary_expr(*it).op()); // still needs typechecking
292  }
293  }
294  else if(expr.id()==ID_initializer_list)
295  {
296  // already fine, just set some type
297  expr.type()=void_type();
298  }
299  else if(
300  expr.id() == ID_forall || expr.id() == ID_exists || expr.id() == ID_lambda)
301  {
302  // These have two operands.
303  // op0 is a tuple with declarations,
304  // op1 is the bound expression
305  auto &binary_expr = to_binary_expr(expr);
306  auto &bindings = binary_expr.op0().operands();
307  auto &where = binary_expr.op1();
308 
309  for(const auto &binding : bindings)
310  {
311  if(binding.get(ID_statement) != ID_decl)
312  {
313  error().source_location = expr.source_location();
314  error() << "expected declaration as operand of quantifier" << eom;
315  throw 0;
316  }
317  }
318 
319  if(has_subexpr(where, ID_side_effect))
320  {
321  error().source_location = expr.source_location();
322  error() << "quantifier must not contain side effects" << eom;
323  throw 0;
324  }
325 
326  // replace declarations by symbol expressions
327  for(auto &binding : bindings)
328  binding = to_code_frontend_decl(to_code(binding)).symbol();
329 
330  if(expr.id() == ID_lambda)
331  {
332  mathematical_function_typet::domaint domain;
333 
334  for(auto &binding : bindings)
335  domain.push_back(binding.type());
336 
337  expr.type() = mathematical_function_typet(domain, where.type());
338  }
339  else
340  {
341  expr.type() = bool_typet();
342  implicit_typecast_bool(where);
343  }
344  }
345  else if(expr.id()==ID_label)
346  {
347  expr.type()=void_type();
348  }
349  else if(expr.id()==ID_array)
350  {
351  // these pop up as string constants, and are already typed
352  }
353  else if(expr.id()==ID_complex)
354  {
355  // these should only exist as constants,
356  // and should already be typed
357  }
358  else if(expr.id() == ID_complex_real)
359  {
360  const exprt &op = to_unary_expr(expr).op();
361 
362  if(op.type().id() != ID_complex)
363  {
364  if(!is_number(op.type()))
365  {
366  error().source_location = op.source_location();
367  error() << "real part retrieval expects numerical operand, "
368  << "but got '" << to_string(op.type()) << "'" << eom;
369  throw 0;
370  }
371 
372  typecast_exprt typecast_expr(op, complex_typet(op.type()));
373  complex_real_exprt complex_real_expr(typecast_expr);
374 
375  expr.swap(complex_real_expr);
376  }
377  else
378  {
379  complex_real_exprt complex_real_expr(op);
380 
381  // these are lvalues if the operand is one
382  if(op.get_bool(ID_C_lvalue))
383  complex_real_expr.set(ID_C_lvalue, true);
384 
385  if(op.type().get_bool(ID_C_constant))
386  complex_real_expr.type().set(ID_C_constant, true);
387 
388  expr.swap(complex_real_expr);
389  }
390  }
391  else if(expr.id() == ID_complex_imag)
392  {
393  const exprt &op = to_unary_expr(expr).op();
394 
395  if(op.type().id() != ID_complex)
396  {
397  if(!is_number(op.type()))
398  {
399  error().source_location = op.source_location();
400  error() << "real part retrieval expects numerical operand, "
401  << "but got '" << to_string(op.type()) << "'" << eom;
402  throw 0;
403  }
404 
405  typecast_exprt typecast_expr(op, complex_typet(op.type()));
406  complex_imag_exprt complex_imag_expr(typecast_expr);
407 
408  expr.swap(complex_imag_expr);
409  }
410  else
411  {
412  complex_imag_exprt complex_imag_expr(op);
413 
414  // these are lvalues if the operand is one
415  if(op.get_bool(ID_C_lvalue))
416  complex_imag_expr.set(ID_C_lvalue, true);
417 
418  if(op.type().get_bool(ID_C_constant))
419  complex_imag_expr.type().set(ID_C_constant, true);
420 
421  expr.swap(complex_imag_expr);
422  }
423  }
424  else if(expr.id()==ID_generic_selection)
425  {
426  // This is C11.
427  // The operand is already typechecked. Depending
428  // on its type, we return one of the generic associations.
429  auto &op = to_unary_expr(expr).op();
430 
431  // This is one of the few places where it's detectable
432  // that we are using "bool" for boolean operators instead
433  // of "int". We convert for this reason.
434  if(op.is_boolean())
435  op = typecast_exprt(op, signed_int_type());
436 
437  irept::subt &generic_associations=
438  expr.add(ID_generic_associations).get_sub();
439 
440  // first typecheck all types
441  for(auto &irep : generic_associations)
442  {
443  if(irep.get(ID_type_arg) != ID_default)
444  {
445  typet &type = static_cast<typet &>(irep.add(ID_type_arg));
446  typecheck_type(type);
447  }
448  }
449 
450  // first try non-default match
451  exprt default_match=nil_exprt();
452  exprt assoc_match=nil_exprt();
453 
454  const typet &op_type = follow(op.type());
455 
456  for(const auto &irep : generic_associations)
457  {
458  if(irep.get(ID_type_arg) == ID_default)
459  default_match = static_cast<const exprt &>(irep.find(ID_value));
460  else if(
461  op_type == follow(static_cast<const typet &>(irep.find(ID_type_arg))))
462  {
463  assoc_match = static_cast<const exprt &>(irep.find(ID_value));
464  }
465  }
466 
467  if(assoc_match.is_nil())
468  {
469  if(default_match.is_not_nil())
470  expr.swap(default_match);
471  else
472  {
473  error().source_location = expr.source_location();
474  error() << "unmatched generic selection: " << to_string(op.type())
475  << eom;
476  throw 0;
477  }
478  }
479  else
480  expr.swap(assoc_match);
481 
482  // still need to typecheck the result
483  typecheck_expr(expr);
484  }
485  else if(expr.id()==ID_gcc_asm_input ||
486  expr.id()==ID_gcc_asm_output ||
487  expr.id()==ID_gcc_asm_clobbered_register)
488  {
489  }
490  else if(expr.id()==ID_lshr || expr.id()==ID_ashr ||
491  expr.id()==ID_assign_lshr || expr.id()==ID_assign_ashr)
492  {
493  // already type checked
494  }
495  else if(
496  expr.id() == ID_C_spec_assigns || expr.id() == ID_C_spec_frees ||
497  expr.id() == ID_target_list)
498  {
499  // already type checked
500  }
501  else
502  {
503  error().source_location = expr.source_location();
504  error() << "unexpected expression: " << expr.pretty() << eom;
505  throw 0;
506  }
507 }

518 void c_typecheck_baset::typecheck_expr_builtin_va_arg(exprt &expr)
519 {
520  // The first parameter is the va_list, and the second
521  // is the type, which will need to be fixed and checked.
522  // The type is given by the parser as type of the expression.
523 
524  typet arg_type=expr.type();
525  typecheck_type(arg_type);
526 
527  const code_typet new_type(
528  {code_typet::parametert(pointer_type(void_type()))}, std::move(arg_type));
529 
530  exprt arg = to_unary_expr(expr).op();
531 
532  implicit_typecast(arg, pointer_type(void_type()));
533 
534  symbol_exprt function(ID_gcc_builtin_va_arg, new_type);
535  function.add_source_location() = expr.source_location();
536 
537  // turn into function call
538  side_effect_expr_function_callt result(
539  function, {arg}, new_type.return_type(), expr.source_location());
540 
541  expr.swap(result);
542 
543  // Make sure symbol exists, but we have it return void
544  // to avoid collisions of the same symbol with different
545  // types.
546 
547  code_typet symbol_type=new_type;
548  symbol_type.return_type()=void_type();
549 
550  symbolt symbol{ID_gcc_builtin_va_arg, symbol_type, ID_C};
551  symbol.base_name=ID_gcc_builtin_va_arg;
552 
553  symbol_table.insert(std::move(symbol));
554 }

556 void c_typecheck_baset::typecheck_expr_cw_va_arg_typeof(exprt &expr)
557 {
558  // used in Code Warrior via
559  //
560  // __va_arg( <Symbol>, _var_arg_typeof( <Typ> ) )
561  //
562  // where __va_arg is declared as
563  //
564  // extern void* __va_arg(void*, int);
565 
566  typet &type=static_cast<typet &>(expr.add(ID_type_arg));
567  typecheck_type(type);
568 
569  // these return an integer
570  expr.type()=signed_int_type();

573 void c_typecheck_baset::typecheck_expr_builtin_offsetof(exprt &expr)
574 {
575  // these need not be constant, due to array indices!
576 
577  if(!expr.operands().empty())
578  {
579  error().source_location = expr.source_location();
580  error() << "builtin_offsetof expects no operands" << eom;
581  throw 0;
582  }
583 
584  typet &type=static_cast<typet &>(expr.add(ID_type_arg));
585  typecheck_type(type);
586 
587  const exprt &member = static_cast<const exprt &>(expr.add(ID_designator));
588 
589  exprt result=from_integer(0, size_type());
590 
591  for(const auto &op : member.operands())
592  {
593  type = follow(type);
594 
595  if(op.id() == ID_member)
596  {
597  if(type.id()!=ID_union && type.id()!=ID_struct)
598  {
599  error().source_location = expr.source_location();
600  error() << "offsetof of member expects struct/union type, "
601  << "but got '" << to_string(type) << "'" << eom;
602  throw 0;
603  }
604 
605  bool found=false;
606  irep_idt component_name = op.get(ID_component_name);
607 
608  while(!found)
609  {
610  PRECONDITION(type.id() == ID_union || type.id() == ID_struct);
611 
612  const struct_union_typet &struct_union_type=
613  to_struct_union_type(type);
614 
615  // direct member?
616  if(struct_union_type.has_component(component_name))
617  {
618  found=true;
619 
620  if(type.id()==ID_struct)
621  {
622  auto o_opt =
623  member_offset_expr(to_struct_type(type), component_name, *this);
624 
625  if(!o_opt.has_value())
626  {
627  error().source_location = expr.source_location();
628  error() << "offsetof failed to determine offset of '"
629  << component_name << "'" << eom;
630  throw 0;
631  }
632 
633  result = plus_exprt(
634  result,
635  typecast_exprt::conditional_cast(o_opt.value(), size_type()));
636  }
637 
638  type=struct_union_type.get_component(component_name).type();
639  }
640  else
641  {
642  // maybe anonymous?
643  bool found2=false;
644 
645  for(const auto &c : struct_union_type.components())
646  {
647  if(
648  c.get_anonymous() &&
649  (c.type().id() == ID_struct_tag || c.type().id() == ID_union_tag))
650  {
651  if(has_component_rec(c.type(), component_name, *this))
652  {
653  if(type.id()==ID_struct)
654  {
655  auto o_opt = member_offset_expr(
656  to_struct_type(type), c.get_name(), *this);
657 
658  if(!o_opt.has_value())
659  {
660  error().source_location = expr.source_location();
661  error() << "offsetof failed to determine offset of '"
662  << component_name << "'" << eom;
663  throw 0;
664  }
665 
666  result = plus_exprt(
667  result,
668  typecast_exprt::conditional_cast(
669  o_opt.value(), size_type()));
670  }
671 
672  typet tmp = follow(c.type());
673  type=tmp;
674  CHECK_RETURN(type.id() == ID_union || type.id() == ID_struct);
675  found2=true;
676  break; // we run into another iteration of the outer loop
677  }
678  }
679  }
680 
681  if(!found2)
682  {
683  error().source_location = expr.source_location();
684  error() << "offset-of of member failed to find component '"
685  << component_name << "' in '" << to_string(type) << "'"
686  << eom;
687  throw 0;
688  }
689  }
690  }
691  }
692  else if(op.id() == ID_index)
693  {
694  if(type.id()!=ID_array)
695  {
696  error().source_location = expr.source_location();
697  error() << "offsetof of index expects array type" << eom;
698  throw 0;
699  }
700 
701  exprt index = to_unary_expr(op).op();
702 
703  // still need to typecheck index
704  typecheck_expr(index);
705 
706  auto element_size_opt =
707  size_of_expr(to_array_type(type).element_type(), *this);
708 
709  if(!element_size_opt.has_value())
710  {
711  error().source_location = expr.source_location();
712  error() << "offsetof failed to determine array element size" << eom;
713  throw 0;
714  }
715 
716  index = typecast_exprt::conditional_cast(index, size_type());
717 
718  result = plus_exprt(result, mult_exprt(element_size_opt.value(), index));
719 
720  typet tmp = to_array_type(type).element_type();
721  type=tmp;
722  }
723  }
724 
725  // We make an effort to produce a constant,
726  // but this may depend on variables
727  simplify(result, *this);
728  result.add_source_location()=expr.source_location();
729 
730  expr.swap(result);
731 }
732 
733 void c_typecheck_baset::typecheck_expr_operands(exprt &expr)
734 {
735  if(expr.id()==ID_side_effect &&
736  expr.get(ID_statement)==ID_function_call)
737  {
738  // don't do function operand
739  typecheck_expr(to_binary_expr(expr).op1()); // arguments
740  }
741  else if(expr.id()==ID_side_effect &&
742  expr.get(ID_statement)==ID_statement_expression)
743  {
744  typecheck_code(to_side_effect_expr_statement_expression(expr).statement());
745  }
746  else if(
747  expr.id() == ID_forall || expr.id() == ID_exists || expr.id() == ID_lambda)
748  {
749  // These introduce new symbols, which need to be added to the symbol table
750  // before the second operand is typechecked.
751 
752  auto &binary_expr = to_binary_expr(expr);
753  auto &bindings = binary_expr.op0().operands();
754 
755  for(auto &binding : bindings)
756  {
757  ansi_c_declarationt &declaration = to_ansi_c_declaration(binding);
758 
759  typecheck_declaration(declaration);
760 
761  if(declaration.declarators().size() != 1)
762  {
763  error().source_location = expr.source_location();
764  error() << "forall/exists expects one declarator exactly" << eom;
765  throw 0;
766  }
767 
768  irep_idt identifier = declaration.declarators().front().get_name();
769 
770  // look it up
771  symbol_table_baset::symbolst::const_iterator s_it =
772  symbol_table.symbols.find(identifier);
773 
774  if(s_it == symbol_table.symbols.end())
775  {
776  error().source_location = expr.source_location();
777  error() << "failed to find bound symbol `" << identifier
778  << "' in symbol table" << eom;
779  throw 0;
780  }
781 
782  const symbolt &symbol = s_it->second;
783 
784  if(
785  symbol.is_type || symbol.is_extern || symbol.is_static_lifetime ||
786  !is_complete_type(symbol.type) || symbol.type.id() == ID_code)
787  {
788  error().source_location = expr.source_location();
789  error() << "unexpected quantified symbol" << eom;
790  throw 0;
791  }
792 
793  code_frontend_declt decl(symbol.symbol_expr());
794  decl.add_source_location() = declaration.source_location();
795 
796  binding = decl;
797  }
798 
799  typecheck_expr(binary_expr.op1());
800  }
801  else
802  {
803  Forall_operands(it, expr)
804  typecheck_expr(*it);
805  }
806 }

808 void c_typecheck_baset::typecheck_expr_symbol(exprt &expr)
809 {
810  irep_idt identifier=to_symbol_expr(expr).get_identifier();
811 
812  // Is it a parameter? We do this while checking parameter lists.
813  id_type_mapt::const_iterator p_it=parameter_map.find(identifier);
814  if(p_it!=parameter_map.end())
815  {
816  // yes
817  expr.type()=p_it->second;
818  expr.set(ID_C_lvalue, true);
819  return;
820  }
821 
822  // renaming via GCC asm label
823  asm_label_mapt::const_iterator entry=
824  asm_label_map.find(identifier);
825  if(entry!=asm_label_map.end())
826  {
827  identifier=entry->second;
828  to_symbol_expr(expr).set_identifier(identifier);
829  }
830 
831  // look it up
832  const symbolt *symbol_ptr;
833  if(lookup(identifier, symbol_ptr))
834  {
835  error().source_location = expr.source_location();
836  error() << "failed to find symbol '" << identifier << "'" << eom;
837  throw 0;
838  }
839 
840  const symbolt &symbol=*symbol_ptr;
841 
842  if(symbol.is_type)
843  {
844  error().source_location = expr.source_location();
845  error() << "did not expect a type symbol here, but got '"
846  << symbol.display_name() << "'" << eom;
847  throw 0;
848  }
849 
850  // save the source location
851  source_locationt source_location=expr.source_location();
852 
853  if(symbol.is_macro)
854  {
855  // preserve enum key
856  #if 0
857  irep_idt base_name=expr.get(ID_C_base_name);
858  #endif
859 
860  follow_macros(expr);
861 
862  #if 0
863  if(expr.is_constant() && !base_name.empty())
864  expr.set(ID_C_cformat, base_name);
865  else
866  #endif
867  typecheck_expr(expr);
868 
869  // preserve location
870  expr.add_source_location()=source_location;
871  }
872  else if(identifier.starts_with(CPROVER_PREFIX "constant_infinity"))
873  {
874  expr=infinity_exprt(symbol.type);
875 
876  // put it back
877  expr.add_source_location()=source_location;
878  }
879  else if(identifier=="__func__" ||
880  identifier=="__FUNCTION__" ||
881  identifier=="__PRETTY_FUNCTION__")
882  {
883  // __func__ is an ANSI-C standard compliant hack to get the function name
884  // __FUNCTION__ and __PRETTY_FUNCTION__ are GCC-specific
885  string_constantt s(source_location.get_function());
886  s.add_source_location()=source_location;
887  s.set(ID_C_lvalue, true);
888  expr.swap(s);
889  }
890  else
891  {
892  expr=symbol.symbol_expr();
893 
894  // put it back
895  expr.add_source_location()=source_location;
896 
897  if(symbol.is_lvalue)
898  expr.set(ID_C_lvalue, true);
899 
900  if(expr.type().id()==ID_code) // function designator
901  { // special case: this is sugar for &f
902  address_of_exprt tmp(expr, pointer_type(expr.type()));
903  tmp.set(ID_C_implicit, true);
904  tmp.add_source_location()=expr.source_location();
905  expr=tmp;
906  }
907  }
908 }

910 void c_typecheck_baset::typecheck_side_effect_statement_expression(
911  side_effect_exprt &expr)
912 {
913  codet &code = to_code(to_unary_expr(expr).op());
914 
915  // the type is the type of the last statement in the
916  // block, but do worry about labels!
917 
918  codet &last=to_code_block(code).find_last_statement();
919 
920  irep_idt last_statement=last.get_statement();
921 
922  if(last_statement==ID_expression)
923  {
924  PRECONDITION(last.operands().size() == 1);
925  exprt &op=last.op0();
926 
927  // arrays here turn into pointers (array decay)
928  if(op.type().id()==ID_array)
929  implicit_typecast(
930  op, pointer_type(to_array_type(op.type()).element_type()));
931 
932  expr.type()=op.type();
933  }
934  else
935  {
936  // we used to do this, but don't expect it any longer
937  PRECONDITION(last_statement != ID_function_call);
938 
939  expr.type()=typet(ID_empty);
940  }
941 }

943 void c_typecheck_baset::typecheck_expr_sizeof(exprt &expr)
944 {
945  typet type;
946 
947  // these come in two flavors: with zero operands, for a type,
948  // and with one operand, for an expression.
949  PRECONDITION(expr.operands().size() <= 1);
950 
951  if(expr.operands().empty())
952  {
953  type.swap(static_cast<typet &>(expr.add(ID_type_arg)));
954  typecheck_type(type);
955  }
956  else
957  {
958  const exprt &op = to_unary_expr(as_const(expr)).op();
959  // This is one of the few places where it's detectable
960  // that we are using "bool" for boolean operators instead
961  // of "int". We convert for this reason.
962  if(op.is_boolean())
963  type = signed_int_type();
964  else
965  type = op.type();
966  }
967 
968  exprt new_expr;
969 
970  if(type.id()==ID_c_bit_field)
971  {
972  // only comma or side-effect expressions are permitted
973  const exprt &op = skip_typecast(to_unary_expr(as_const(expr)).op());
974  if(op.id() == ID_comma || op.id() == ID_side_effect)
975  {
976  const c_bit_field_typet &bf_type = to_c_bit_field_type(type);
977  if(config.ansi_c.mode == configt::ansi_ct::flavourt::GCC)
978  {
979  new_expr = from_integer(
980  (bf_type.get_width() + config.ansi_c.char_width - 1) /
981  config.ansi_c.char_width,
982  size_type());
983  }
984  else
985  {
986  auto size_of_opt = size_of_expr(bf_type.underlying_type(), *this);
987 
988  if(!size_of_opt.has_value())
989  {
990  error().source_location = expr.source_location();
991  error() << "type has no size: "
992  << to_string(bf_type.underlying_type()) << eom;
993  throw 0;
994  }
995 
996  new_expr = size_of_opt.value();
997  }
998  }
999  else
1000  {
1001  error().source_location = expr.source_location();
1002  error() << "sizeof cannot be applied to bit fields" << eom;
1003  throw 0;
1004  }
1005  }
1006  else if(type.id() == ID_bool)
1007  {
1008  error().source_location = expr.source_location();
1009  error() << "sizeof cannot be applied to single bits" << eom;
1010  throw 0;
1011  }
1012  else if(type.id() == ID_empty)
1013  {
1014  // This is a gcc extension.
1015  // https://gcc.gnu.org/onlinedocs/gcc-4.8.0/gcc/Pointer-Arith.html
1016  new_expr = from_integer(1, size_type());
1017  }
1018  else
1019  {
1020  if(
1021  (type.id() == ID_struct_tag &&
1022  follow_tag(to_struct_tag_type(type)).is_incomplete()) ||
1023  (type.id() == ID_union_tag &&
1024  follow_tag(to_union_tag_type(type)).is_incomplete()) ||
1025  (type.id() == ID_c_enum_tag &&
1026  follow_tag(to_c_enum_tag_type(type)).is_incomplete()) ||
1027  (type.id() == ID_array && to_array_type(type).is_incomplete()))
1028  {
1029  error().source_location = expr.source_location();
1030  error() << "invalid application of \'sizeof\' to an incomplete type\n\t\'"
1031  << to_string(type) << "\'" << eom;
1032  throw 0;
1033  }
1034 
1035  auto size_of_opt = size_of_expr(type, *this);
1036 
1037  if(!size_of_opt.has_value())
1038  {
1039  error().source_location = expr.source_location();
1040  error() << "type has no size: " << to_string(type) << eom;
1041  throw 0;
1042  }
1043 
1044  new_expr = size_of_opt.value();
1045  }
1046 
1047  source_locationt location = expr.source_location();
1048  new_expr.swap(expr);
1049  expr.add_source_location() = location;
1050  expr.add(ID_C_c_sizeof_type)=type;
1051 
1052  // The type may contain side-effects.
1053  if(!clean_code.empty())
1054  {
1055  side_effect_exprt side_effect_expr(
1056  ID_statement_expression, void_type(), location);
1057  auto decl_block=code_blockt::from_list(clean_code);
1058  decl_block.set_statement(ID_decl_block);
1059  side_effect_expr.copy_to_operands(decl_block);
1060  clean_code.clear();
1061 
1062  // We merge the side-effect into the operand of the typecast,
1063  // using a comma-expression.
1064  // I.e., (type)e becomes (type)(side-effect, e)
1065  // It is not obvious whether the type or 'e' should be evaluated
1066  // first.
1067 
1068  exprt comma_expr =
1069  binary_exprt{std::move(side_effect_expr), ID_comma, expr, expr.type()}
1070  .with_source_location(location);
1071  expr.swap(comma_expr);
1072  }
1073 }

1075 void c_typecheck_baset::typecheck_expr_alignof(exprt &expr)
1076 {
1077  typet argument_type;
1078 
1079  if(expr.operands().size()==1)
1080  argument_type = to_unary_expr(expr).op().type();
1081  else
1082  {
1083  typet &op_type=static_cast<typet &>(expr.add(ID_type_arg));
1084  typecheck_type(op_type);
1085  argument_type=op_type;
1086  }
1087 
1088  // we only care about the type
1089  mp_integer a=alignment(argument_type, *this);
1090 
1091  exprt tmp=from_integer(a, size_type());
1092  tmp.add_source_location()=expr.source_location();
1093 
1094  expr.swap(tmp);
1095 }

1097 void c_typecheck_baset::typecheck_expr_typecast(exprt &expr)
1098 {
1099  exprt &op = to_unary_expr(expr).op();
1100 
1101  typecheck_type(expr.type());
1102 
1103  // The type may contain side-effects.
1104  if(!clean_code.empty())
1105  {
1106  side_effect_exprt side_effect_expr(
1107  ID_statement_expression, void_type(), expr.source_location());
1108  auto decl_block=code_blockt::from_list(clean_code);
1109  decl_block.set_statement(ID_decl_block);
1110  side_effect_expr.copy_to_operands(decl_block);
1111  clean_code.clear();
1112 
1113  // We merge the side-effect into the operand of the typecast,
1114  // using a comma-expression.
1115  // I.e., (type)e becomes (type)(side-effect, e)
1116  // It is not obvious whether the type or 'e' should be evaluated
1117  // first.
1118 
1119  binary_exprt comma_expr{
1120  std::move(side_effect_expr), ID_comma, op, op.type()};
1121  op.swap(comma_expr);
1122  }
1123 
1124  const typet expr_type = expr.type();
1125 
1126  if(
1127  expr_type.id() == ID_union_tag && expr_type != op.type() &&
1128  op.id() != ID_initializer_list)
1129  {
1130  // This is a GCC extension. It's either a 'temporary union',
1131  // where the argument is one of the member types.
1132 
1133  // This is one of the few places where it's detectable
1134  // that we are using "bool" for boolean operators instead
1135  // of "int". We convert for this reason.
1136  if(op.is_boolean())
1137  op = typecast_exprt(op, signed_int_type());
1138 
1139  // we need to find a member with the right type
1140  const auto &union_type = follow_tag(to_union_tag_type(expr_type));
1141  for(const auto &c : union_type.components())
1142  {
1143  if(c.type() == op.type())
1144  {
1145  // found! build union constructor
1146  union_exprt union_expr(c.get_name(), op, expr.type());
1147  union_expr.add_source_location()=expr.source_location();
1148  expr=union_expr;
1149  expr.set(ID_C_lvalue, true);
1150  return;
1151  }
1152  }
1153 
1154  // not found, complain
1155  error().source_location = expr.source_location();
1156  error() << "type cast to union: type '" << to_string(op.type())
1157  << "' not found in union" << eom;
1158  throw 0;
1159  }
1160 
1161  // We allow (TYPE){ initializer_list }
1162  // This is called "compound literal", and is syntactic
1163  // sugar for a (possibly local) declaration.
1164  if(op.id()==ID_initializer_list)
1165  {
1166  // just do a normal initialization
1167  do_initializer(op, expr.type(), false);
1168 
1169  // This produces a struct-expression,
1170  // union-expression, array-expression,
1171  // or an expression for a pointer or scalar.
1172  // We produce a compound_literal expression.
1173  exprt tmp(ID_compound_literal, expr.type());
1174  tmp.copy_to_operands(op);
1175 
1176  // handle the case of TYPE being an array with unspecified size
1177  if(op.id()==ID_array &&
1178  expr.type().id()==ID_array &&
1179  to_array_type(expr.type()).size().is_nil())
1180  tmp.type()=op.type();
1181 
1182  expr=tmp;
1183  expr.set(ID_C_lvalue, true); // these are l-values
1184  return;
1185  }
1186 
1187  // a cast to void is always fine
1188  if(expr_type.id()==ID_empty)
1189  return;
1190 
1191  const typet op_type = op.type();
1192 
1193  // cast to same type?
1194  if(expr_type == op_type)
1195  return; // it's ok
1196 
1197  // vectors?
1198 
1199  if(expr_type.id()==ID_vector)
1200  {
1201  // we are generous -- any vector to vector is fine
1202  if(op_type.id()==ID_vector)
1203  return;
1204  else if(op_type.id()==ID_signedbv ||
1205  op_type.id()==ID_unsignedbv)
1206  return;
1207  }
1208 
1209  if(!is_numeric_type(expr_type) && expr_type.id()!=ID_pointer)
1210  {
1211  error().source_location = expr.source_location();
1212  error() << "type cast to '" << to_string(expr_type) << "' is not permitted"
1213  << eom;
1214  throw 0;
1215  }
1216 
1217  if(is_numeric_type(op_type) || op_type.id()==ID_pointer)
1218  {
1219  }
1220  else if(op_type.id()==ID_array)
1221  {
1222  // This is the promotion from an array
1223  // to a pointer to the first element.
1224  auto error_opt = c_typecastt::check_address_can_be_taken(op_type);
1225  if(error_opt.has_value())
1226  throw invalid_source_file_exceptiont{*error_opt, expr.source_location()};
1227 
1228  index_exprt index(op, from_integer(0, c_index_type()));
1229  op=address_of_exprt(index);
1230  }
1231  else if(op_type.id()==ID_empty)
1232  {
1233  if(expr_type.id()!=ID_empty)
1234  {
1235  error().source_location = expr.source_location();
1236  error() << "type cast from void only permitted to void, but got '"
1237  << to_string(expr.type()) << "'" << eom;
1238  throw 0;
1239  }
1240  }
1241  else if(op_type.id()==ID_vector)
1242  {
1243  const vector_typet &op_vector_type=
1244  to_vector_type(op_type);
1245 
1246  // gcc allows conversion of a vector of size 1 to
1247  // an integer/float of the same size
1248  if((expr_type.id()==ID_signedbv ||
1249  expr_type.id()==ID_unsignedbv) &&
1250  pointer_offset_bits(expr_type, *this)==
1251  pointer_offset_bits(op_vector_type, *this))
1252  {
1253  }
1254  else
1255  {
1256  error().source_location = expr.source_location();
1257  error() << "type cast from vector to '" << to_string(expr.type())
1258  << "' not permitted" << eom;
1259  throw 0;
1260  }
1261  }
1262  else
1263  {
1264  error().source_location = expr.source_location();
1265  error() << "type cast from '" << to_string(op_type) << "' not permitted"
1266  << eom;
1267  throw 0;
1268  }
1269 
1270  // The new thing is an lvalue if the previous one is
1271  // an lvalue and it's just a pointer type cast.
1272  // This isn't really standard conformant!
1273  // Note that gcc says "warning: target of assignment not really an lvalue;
1274  // this will be a hard error in the future", i.e., we
1275  // can hope that the code below will one day simply go away.
1276 
1277  // Current versions of gcc in fact refuse to do this! Yay!
1278 
1279  if(op.get_bool(ID_C_lvalue))
1280  {
1281  if(expr_type.id()==ID_pointer)
1282  expr.set(ID_C_lvalue, true);
1283  }
1284 }

1286 void c_typecheck_baset::make_index_type(exprt &expr)
1287 {
1288  implicit_typecast(expr, c_index_type());
1289 }
1290 
1291 void c_typecheck_baset::typecheck_expr_index(exprt &expr)
1292 {
1293  exprt &array_expr = to_binary_expr(expr).op0();
1294  exprt &index_expr = to_binary_expr(expr).op1();
1295 
1296  // we might have to swap them
1297 
1298  {
1299  const typet &array_type = array_expr.type();
1300  const typet &index_type = index_expr.type();
1301 
1302  if(
1303  array_type.id() != ID_array && array_type.id() != ID_pointer &&
1304  array_type.id() != ID_vector &&
1305  (index_type.id() == ID_array || index_type.id() == ID_pointer ||
1306  index_type.id() == ID_vector))
1307  std::swap(array_expr, index_expr);
1308  }
1309 
1310  make_index_type(index_expr);
1311 
1312  // array_expr is a reference to one of expr.operands(), when that vector is
1313  // swapped below the reference is no longer valid. final_array_type exists
1314  // beyond that point so can't be a reference
1315  const typet final_array_type = array_expr.type();
1316 
1317  if(final_array_type.id()==ID_array ||
1318  final_array_type.id()==ID_vector)
1319  {
1320  expr.type() = to_type_with_subtype(final_array_type).subtype();
1321 
1322  if(array_expr.get_bool(ID_C_lvalue))
1323  expr.set(ID_C_lvalue, true);
1324 
1325  if(final_array_type.get_bool(ID_C_constant))
1326  expr.type().set(ID_C_constant, true);
1327  }
1328  else if(final_array_type.id()==ID_pointer)
1329  {
1330  // p[i] is syntactic sugar for *(p+i)
1331 
1332  typecheck_arithmetic_pointer(to_binary_expr(expr).op0());
1333  exprt::operandst summands;
1334  std::swap(summands, expr.operands());
1335  expr.add_to_operands(plus_exprt(std::move(summands), array_expr.type()));
1336  expr.id(ID_dereference);
1337  expr.set(ID_C_lvalue, true);
1338  expr.type() = to_pointer_type(final_array_type).base_type();
1339  }
1340  else
1341  {
1342  error().source_location = expr.source_location();
1343  error() << "operator [] must take array/vector or pointer but got '"
1344  << to_string(array_expr.type()) << "'" << eom;
1345  throw 0;
1346  }
1347 }
1348 
1349 void c_typecheck_baset::adjust_float_rel(binary_relation_exprt &expr)
1350 {
1351  // equality and disequality on float is not mathematical equality!
1352  if(expr.op0().type().id() == ID_floatbv)
1353  {
1354  if(expr.id()==ID_equal)
1355  expr.id(ID_ieee_float_equal);
1356  else if(expr.id()==ID_notequal)
1357  expr.id(ID_ieee_float_notequal);
1358  }
1359 }
1360 
1361 void c_typecheck_baset::typecheck_expr_rel(
1362  binary_relation_exprt &expr)
1363 {
1364  exprt &op0=expr.op0();
1365  exprt &op1=expr.op1();
1366 
1367  const typet o_type0=op0.type();
1368  const typet o_type1=op1.type();
1369 
1370  if(o_type0.id() == ID_vector || o_type1.id() == ID_vector)
1371  {
1372  typecheck_expr_rel_vector(expr);
1373  return;
1374  }
1375 
1376  expr.type()=bool_typet();
1377 
1378  if(expr.id()==ID_equal || expr.id()==ID_notequal)
1379  {
1380  if(follow(o_type0)==follow(o_type1))
1381  {
1382  if(o_type0.id() != ID_array)
1383  {
1384  adjust_float_rel(expr);
1385  return; // no promotion necessary
1386  }
1387  }
1388  }
1389 
1390  implicit_typecast_arithmetic(op0, op1);
1391 
1392  const typet &type0=op0.type();
1393  const typet &type1=op1.type();
1394 
1395  if(type0==type1)
1396  {
1397  if(is_number(type0))
1398  {
1399  adjust_float_rel(expr);
1400  return;
1401  }
1402 
1403  if(type0.id()==ID_pointer)
1404  {
1405  if(expr.id()==ID_equal || expr.id()==ID_notequal)
1406  return;
1407 
1408  if(expr.id()==ID_le || expr.id()==ID_lt ||
1409  expr.id()==ID_ge || expr.id()==ID_gt)
1410  return;
1411  }
1412 
1413  if(type0.id()==ID_string_constant)
1414  {
1415  if(expr.id()==ID_equal || expr.id()==ID_notequal)
1416  return;
1417  }
1418  }
1419  else
1420  {
1421  // pointer and zero
1422  if(type0.id()==ID_pointer &&
1423  simplify_expr(op1, *this).is_zero())
1424  {
1425  op1 = null_pointer_exprt{to_pointer_type(type0)};
1426  return;
1427  }
1428 
1429  if(type1.id()==ID_pointer &&
1430  simplify_expr(op0, *this).is_zero())
1431  {
1432  op0 = null_pointer_exprt{to_pointer_type(type1)};
1433  return;
1434  }
1435 
1436  // pointer and integer
1437  if(type0.id()==ID_pointer && is_number(type1))
1438  {
1439  op1 = typecast_exprt(op1, type0);
1440  return;
1441  }
1442 
1443  if(type1.id()==ID_pointer && is_number(type0))
1444  {
1445  op0 = typecast_exprt(op0, type1);
1446  return;
1447  }
1448 
1449  if(type0.id()==ID_pointer && type1.id()==ID_pointer)
1450  {
1451  op1 = typecast_exprt(op1, type0);
1452  return;
1453  }
1454  }
1455 
1456  error().source_location = expr.source_location();
1457  error() << "operator '" << expr.id() << "' not defined for types '"
1458  << to_string(o_type0) << "' and '" << to_string(o_type1) << "'"
1459  << eom;
1460  throw 0;
1461 }
1462 
1463 void c_typecheck_baset::typecheck_expr_rel_vector(binary_exprt &expr)
1464 {
1465  const typet &o_type0 = as_const(expr).op0().type();
1466  const typet &o_type1 = as_const(expr).op1().type();
1467 
1468  if(o_type0.id() != ID_vector || o_type0 != o_type1)
1469  {
1470  error().source_location = expr.source_location();
1471  error() << "vector operator '" << expr.id() << "' not defined for types '"
1472  << to_string(o_type0) << "' and '" << to_string(o_type1) << "'"
1473  << eom;
1474  throw 0;
1475  }
1476 
1477  // Comparisons between vectors produce a vector of integers of the same width
1478  // with the same dimension.
1479  auto subtype_width =
1480  to_bitvector_type(to_vector_type(o_type0).element_type()).get_width();
1481  expr.type() = vector_typet{
1482  to_vector_type(o_type0).index_type(),
1483  signedbv_typet{subtype_width},
1484  to_vector_type(o_type0).size()};
1485 
1486  // Replace the id as the semantics of these are point-wise application (and
1487  // the result is not of bool type).
1488  if(expr.id() == ID_notequal)
1489  expr.id(ID_vector_notequal);
1490  else
1491  expr.id("vector-" + id2string(expr.id()));
1492 }

1494 void c_typecheck_baset::typecheck_expr_ptrmember(exprt &expr)
1495 {
1496  auto &op = to_unary_expr(expr).op();
1497  const typet &op0_type = op.type();
1498 
1499  if(op0_type.id() == ID_array)
1500  {
1501  // a->f is the same as a[0].f
1502  exprt zero = from_integer(0, c_index_type());
1503  index_exprt index_expr(op, zero, to_array_type(op0_type).element_type());
1504  index_expr.set(ID_C_lvalue, true);
1505  op.swap(index_expr);
1506  }
1507  else if(op0_type.id() == ID_pointer)
1508  {
1509  // turn x->y into (*x).y
1510  dereference_exprt deref_expr(op);
1511  deref_expr.add_source_location()=expr.source_location();
1512  typecheck_expr_dereference(deref_expr);
1513  op.swap(deref_expr);
1514  }
1515  else
1516  {
1517  error().source_location = expr.source_location();
1518  error() << "ptrmember operator requires pointer or array type "
1519  "on left hand side, but got '"
1520  << to_string(op0_type) << "'" << eom;
1521  throw 0;
1522  }
1523 
1524  expr.id(ID_member);
1525  typecheck_expr_member(expr);
1526 }
1527 
1528 void c_typecheck_baset::typecheck_expr_member(exprt &expr)
1529 {
1530  exprt &op0 = to_unary_expr(expr).op();
1531  typet type=op0.type();
1532 
1533  type = follow(type);
1534 
1535  if(type.id()!=ID_struct &&
1536  type.id()!=ID_union)
1537  {
1538  error().source_location = expr.source_location();
1539  error() << "member operator requires structure type "
1540  "on left hand side but got '"
1541  << to_string(type) << "'" << eom;
1542  throw 0;
1543  }
1544 
1545  const struct_union_typet &struct_union_type=
1546  to_struct_union_type(type);
1547 
1548  if(struct_union_type.is_incomplete())
1549  {
1550  error().source_location = expr.source_location();
1551  error() << "member operator got incomplete " << type.id()
1552  << " type on left hand side" << eom;
1553  throw 0;
1554  }
1555 
1556  const irep_idt &component_name=
1557  expr.get(ID_component_name);
1558 
1559  // first try to find directly
1560  const struct_union_typet::componentt &component =
1561  struct_union_type.get_component(component_name);
1562 
1563  // if that fails, search the anonymous members
1564 
1565  if(component.is_nil())
1566  {
1567  exprt tmp=get_component_rec(op0, component_name, *this);
1568 
1569  if(tmp.is_nil())
1570  {
1571  // give up
1572  error().source_location = expr.source_location();
1573  error() << "member '" << component_name << "' not found in '"
1574  << to_string(type) << "'" << eom;
1575  throw 0;
1576  }
1577 
1578  // done!
1579  expr.swap(tmp);
1580  return;
1581  }
1582 
1583  expr.type()=component.type();
1584 
1585  if(op0.get_bool(ID_C_lvalue))
1586  expr.set(ID_C_lvalue, true);
1587 
1588  if(op0.type().get_bool(ID_C_constant) || type.get_bool(ID_C_constant))
1589  expr.type().set(ID_C_constant, true);
1590 
1591  // copy method identifier
1592  const irep_idt &identifier=component.get(ID_C_identifier);
1593 
1594  if(!identifier.empty())
1595  expr.set(ID_C_identifier, identifier);
1596 
1597  const irep_idt &access=component.get_access();
1598 
1599  if(access==ID_private)
1600  {
1601  error().source_location = expr.source_location();
1602  error() << "member '" << component_name << "' is " << access << eom;
1603  throw 0;
1604  }
1605 }
1606 
1607 void c_typecheck_baset::typecheck_expr_trinary(if_exprt &expr)
1608 {
1609  exprt::operandst &operands=expr.operands();
1610 
1611  PRECONDITION(operands.size() == 3);
1612 
1613  // copy (save) original types
1614  const typet o_type0=operands[0].type();
1615  const typet o_type1=operands[1].type();
1616  const typet o_type2=operands[2].type();
1617 
1618  implicit_typecast_bool(operands[0]);
1619 
1620  if(o_type1.id() == ID_empty || o_type2.id() == ID_empty)
1621  {
1622  operands[1] = typecast_exprt::conditional_cast(operands[1], void_type());
1623  operands[2] = typecast_exprt::conditional_cast(operands[2], void_type());
1624  expr.type() = void_type();
1625  return;
1626  }
1627 
1628  if(operands[1].type().id()==ID_pointer &&
1629  operands[2].type().id()!=ID_pointer)
1630  implicit_typecast(operands[2], operands[1].type());
1631  else if(operands[2].type().id()==ID_pointer &&
1632  operands[1].type().id()!=ID_pointer)
1633  implicit_typecast(operands[1], operands[2].type());
1634 
1635  if(operands[1].type().id()==ID_pointer &&
1636  operands[2].type().id()==ID_pointer &&
1637  operands[1].type()!=operands[2].type())
1638  {
1639  exprt tmp1=simplify_expr(operands[1], *this);
1640  exprt tmp2=simplify_expr(operands[2], *this);
1641 
1642  // is one of them void * AND null? Convert that to the other.
1643  // (at least that's how GCC behaves)
1644  if(
1645  to_pointer_type(operands[1].type()).base_type().id() == ID_empty &&
1646  tmp1.is_constant() && is_null_pointer(to_constant_expr(tmp1)))
1647  {
1648  implicit_typecast(operands[1], operands[2].type());
1649  }
1650  else if(
1651  to_pointer_type(operands[2].type()).base_type().id() == ID_empty &&
1652  tmp2.is_constant() && is_null_pointer(to_constant_expr(tmp2)))
1653  {
1654  implicit_typecast(operands[2], operands[1].type());
1655  }
1656  else if(
1657  to_pointer_type(operands[1].type()).base_type().id() != ID_code ||
1658  to_pointer_type(operands[2].type()).base_type().id() != ID_code)
1659  {
1660  // Make it void *.
1661  // gcc and clang issue a warning for this.
1662  expr.type() = pointer_type(void_type());
1663  implicit_typecast(operands[1], expr.type());
1664  implicit_typecast(operands[2], expr.type());
1665  }
1666  else
1667  {
1668  // maybe functions without parameter lists
1669  const code_typet &c_type1 =
1670  to_code_type(to_pointer_type(operands[1].type()).base_type());
1671  const code_typet &c_type2 =
1672  to_code_type(to_pointer_type(operands[2].type()).base_type());
1673 
1674  if(c_type1.return_type()==c_type2.return_type())
1675  {
1676  if(c_type1.parameters().empty() && c_type1.has_ellipsis())
1677  implicit_typecast(operands[1], operands[2].type());
1678  else if(c_type2.parameters().empty() && c_type2.has_ellipsis())
1679  implicit_typecast(operands[2], operands[1].type());
1680  }
1681  }
1682  }
1683 
1684  if(operands[1].type().id()==ID_empty ||
1685  operands[2].type().id()==ID_empty)
1686  {
1687  expr.type()=void_type();
1688  return;
1689  }
1690 
1691  if(
1692  operands[1].type() != operands[2].type() ||
1693  operands[1].type().id() == ID_array)
1694  {
1695  implicit_typecast_arithmetic(operands[1], operands[2]);
1696  }
1697 
1698  if(operands[1].type() == operands[2].type())
1699  {
1700  expr.type()=operands[1].type();
1701 
1702  // GCC says: "A conditional expression is a valid lvalue
1703  // if its type is not void and the true and false branches
1704  // are both valid lvalues."
1705 
1706  if(operands[1].get_bool(ID_C_lvalue) &&
1707  operands[2].get_bool(ID_C_lvalue))
1708  expr.set(ID_C_lvalue, true);
1709 
1710  return;
1711  }
1712 
1713  error().source_location = expr.source_location();
1714  error() << "operator ?: not defined for types '" << to_string(o_type1)
1715  << "' and '" << to_string(o_type2) << "'" << eom;
1716  throw 0;
1717 }
1718 
1719 void c_typecheck_baset::typecheck_side_effect_gcc_conditional_expression(
1720  side_effect_exprt &expr)
1721 {
1722  // x ? : y is almost the same as x ? x : y,
1723  // but not quite, as x is evaluated only once
1724 
1725  exprt::operandst &operands=expr.operands();
1726 
1727  if(operands.size()!=2)
1728  {
1729  error().source_location = expr.source_location();
1730  error() << "gcc conditional_expr expects two operands" << eom;
1731  throw 0;
1732  }
1733 
1734  // use typechecking code for "if"
1735 
1736  if_exprt if_expr(operands[0], operands[0], operands[1]);
1737  if_expr.add_source_location()=expr.source_location();
1738 
1739  typecheck_expr_trinary(if_expr);
1740 
1741  // copy the result
1742  operands[0] = if_expr.true_case();
1743  operands[1] = if_expr.false_case();
1744  expr.type()=if_expr.type();
1745 }

1747 void c_typecheck_baset::typecheck_expr_address_of(exprt &expr)
1748 {
1749  exprt &op = to_unary_expr(expr).op();
1750 
1751  auto error_opt = c_typecastt::check_address_can_be_taken(op.type());
1752 
1753  if(error_opt.has_value())
1754  throw invalid_source_file_exceptiont{*error_opt, expr.source_location()};
1755 
1756  // special case: address of label
1757  if(op.id()==ID_label)
1758  {
1759  expr.type()=pointer_type(void_type());
1760 
1761  // remember the label
1762  labels_used[op.get(ID_identifier)]=op.source_location();
1763  return;
1764  }
1765 
1766  // special case: address of function designator
1767  // ANSI-C 99 section 6.3.2.1 paragraph 4
1768 
1769  if(
1770  op.id() == ID_address_of && op.get_bool(ID_C_implicit) &&
1771  to_address_of_expr(op).object().type().id() == ID_code)
1772  {
1773  // make the implicit address_of an explicit address_of
1774  exprt tmp;
1775  tmp.swap(op);
1776  tmp.set(ID_C_implicit, false);
1777  expr.swap(tmp);
1778  return;
1779  }
1780 
1781  if(op.id()==ID_struct ||
1782  op.id()==ID_union ||
1783  op.id()==ID_array ||
1784  op.id()==ID_string_constant)
1785  {
1786  // these are really objects
1787  }
1788  else if(op.get_bool(ID_C_lvalue))
1789  {
1790  // ok
1791  }
1792  else if(op.type().id()==ID_code)
1793  {
1794  // ok
1795  }
1796  else
1797  {
1798  error().source_location = expr.source_location();
1799  error() << "address_of error: '" << to_string(op) << "' not an lvalue"
1800  << eom;
1801  throw 0;
1802  }
1803 
1804  expr.type()=pointer_type(op.type());
1805 }

1807 void c_typecheck_baset::typecheck_expr_dereference(exprt &expr)
1808 {
1809  exprt &op = to_unary_expr(expr).op();
1810 
1811  const typet op_type = op.type();
1812 
1813  if(op_type.id()==ID_array)
1814  {
1815  // *a is the same as a[0]
1816  expr.id(ID_index);
1817  expr.type() = to_array_type(op_type).element_type();
1818  expr.copy_to_operands(from_integer(0, c_index_type()));
1819  CHECK_RETURN(expr.operands().size() == 2);
1820  }
1821  else if(op_type.id()==ID_pointer)
1822  {
1823  expr.type() = to_pointer_type(op_type).base_type();
1824 
1825  if(
1826  expr.type().id() == ID_empty &&
1827  config.ansi_c.mode == configt::ansi_ct::flavourt::VISUAL_STUDIO)
1828  {
1829  error().source_location = expr.source_location();
1830  error() << "dereferencing void pointer" << eom;
1831  throw 0;
1832  }
1833  }
1834  else
1835  {
1836  error().source_location = expr.source_location();
1837  error() << "operand of unary * '" << to_string(op)
1838  << "' is not a pointer, but got '" << to_string(op_type) << "'"
1839  << eom;
1840  throw 0;
1841  }
1842 
1843  expr.set(ID_C_lvalue, true);
1844 
1845  // if you dereference a pointer pointing to
1846  // a function, you get a pointer again
1847  // allowing ******...*p
1848 
1849  typecheck_expr_function_identifier(expr);
1850 }
1851 
1852 void c_typecheck_baset::typecheck_expr_function_identifier(exprt &expr)
1853 {
1854  if(expr.type().id()==ID_code)
1855  {
1856  address_of_exprt tmp(expr, pointer_type(expr.type()));
1857  tmp.set(ID_C_implicit, true);
1858  tmp.add_source_location()=expr.source_location();
1859  expr=tmp;
1860  }
1861 }
1862 
1863 void c_typecheck_baset::typecheck_expr_side_effect(side_effect_exprt &expr)
1864 {
1865  const irep_idt &statement=expr.get_statement();
1866 
1867  if(statement==ID_preincrement ||
1868  statement==ID_predecrement ||
1869  statement==ID_postincrement ||
1870  statement==ID_postdecrement)
1871  {
1872  const exprt &op0 = to_unary_expr(expr).op();
1873  const typet &type0=op0.type();
1874 
1875  if(!op0.get_bool(ID_C_lvalue))
1876  {
1877  error().source_location = op0.source_location();
1878  error() << "prefix operator error: '" << to_string(op0)
1879  << "' not an lvalue" << eom;
1880  throw 0;
1881  }
1882 
1883  if(type0.get_bool(ID_C_constant))
1884  {
1885  error().source_location = op0.source_location();
1886  error() << "'" << to_string(op0) << "' is constant" << eom;
1887  throw 0;
1888  }
1889 
1890  if(type0.id() == ID_c_enum_tag)
1891  {
1892  const c_enum_typet &enum_type = follow_tag(to_c_enum_tag_type(type0));
1893  if(enum_type.is_incomplete())
1894  {
1895  error().source_location = expr.source_location();
1896  error() << "operator '" << statement << "' given incomplete type '"
1897  << to_string(type0) << "'" << eom;
1898  throw 0;
1899  }
1900 
1901  // increment/decrement on underlying type
1902  to_unary_expr(expr).op() =
1903  typecast_exprt(op0, enum_type.underlying_type());
1904  expr.type() = enum_type.underlying_type();
1905  }
1906  else if(type0.id() == ID_c_bit_field)
1907  {
1908  // promote to underlying type
1909  typet underlying_type = to_c_bit_field_type(type0).underlying_type();
1910  typet type_before{type0};
1911  to_unary_expr(expr).op() = typecast_exprt(op0, underlying_type);
1912  expr.type()=underlying_type;
1913  typecast_exprt result{expr, type_before};
1914  expr.swap(result);
1915  }
1916  else if(type0.id() == ID_bool || type0.id() == ID_c_bool)
1917  {
1918  implicit_typecast_arithmetic(to_unary_expr(expr).op());
1919  expr.type() = op0.type();
1920  }
1921  else if(is_numeric_type(type0))
1922  {
1923  expr.type()=type0;
1924  }
1925  else if(type0.id() == ID_pointer)
1926  {
1927  typecheck_arithmetic_pointer(to_unary_expr(expr).op());
1928  expr.type() = to_unary_expr(expr).op().type();
1929  }
1930  else
1931  {
1932  error().source_location = expr.source_location();
1933  error() << "operator '" << statement << "' not defined for type '"
1934  << to_string(type0) << "'" << eom;
1935  throw 0;
1936  }
1937  }
1938  else if(statement.starts_with("assign"))
1939  typecheck_side_effect_assignment(expr);
1940  else if(statement==ID_function_call)
1941  typecheck_side_effect_function_call(
1942  to_side_effect_expr_function_call(expr));
1943  else if(statement==ID_statement_expression)
1944  typecheck_side_effect_statement_expression(expr);
1945  else if(statement==ID_gcc_conditional_expression)
1946  typecheck_side_effect_gcc_conditional_expression(expr);
1947  else
1948  {
1949  error().source_location = expr.source_location();
1950  error() << "unknown side effect: " << statement << eom;
1951  throw 0;
1952  }
1953 }
1954 
1955 void c_typecheck_baset::typecheck_typed_target_call(
1956  side_effect_expr_function_callt &expr)
1957 {
1958  INVARIANT(
1959  expr.function().id() == ID_symbol &&
1960  to_symbol_expr(expr.function()).get_identifier() == CPROVER_PREFIX
1961  "typed_target",
1962  "expression must be a " CPROVER_PREFIX "typed_target function call");
1963 
1964  auto &f_op = to_symbol_expr(expr.function());
1965 
1966  if(expr.arguments().size() != 1)
1967  {
1968  throw invalid_source_file_exceptiont{
1969  "expected 1 argument for " CPROVER_PREFIX "typed_target, found " +
1970  std::to_string(expr.arguments().size()),
1971  expr.source_location()};
1972  }
1973 
1974  auto arg0 = expr.arguments().front();
1975 
1976  if(!is_assignable(arg0) || !arg0.get_bool(ID_C_lvalue))
1977  {
1978  throw invalid_source_file_exceptiont{
1979  "argument of " CPROVER_PREFIX "typed_target must be assignable",
1980  arg0.source_location()};
1981  }
1982 
1983  const auto &size = size_of_expr(arg0.type(), *this);
1984  if(!size.has_value())
1985  {
1986  throw invalid_source_file_exceptiont{
1987  "sizeof not defined for argument of " CPROVER_PREFIX
1988  "typed_target of type " +
1989  to_string(arg0.type()),
1990  arg0.source_location()};
1991  }
1992 
1993  // rewrite call to "assignable"
1994  f_op.set_identifier(CPROVER_PREFIX "assignable");
1995  exprt::operandst arguments;
1996  // pointer
1997  arguments.push_back(address_of_exprt(arg0));
1998  // size
1999  arguments.push_back(size.value());
2000  // is_pointer
2001  if(arg0.type().id() == ID_pointer)
2002  arguments.push_back(true_exprt());
2003  else
2004  arguments.push_back(false_exprt());
2005 
2006  expr.arguments().swap(arguments);
2007  expr.type() = empty_typet();
2008 }

2010 void c_typecheck_baset::typecheck_obeys_contract_call(
2011  side_effect_expr_function_callt &expr)
2012 {
2013  INVARIANT(
2014  expr.function().id() == ID_symbol &&
2015  to_symbol_expr(expr.function()).get_identifier() == CPROVER_PREFIX
2016  "obeys_contract",
2017  "expression must be a " CPROVER_PREFIX "obeys_contract function call");
2018 
2019  if(expr.arguments().size() != 2)
2020  {
2021  throw invalid_source_file_exceptiont{
2022  "expected 2 arguments for " CPROVER_PREFIX "obeys_contract, found " +
2023  std::to_string(expr.arguments().size()),
2024  expr.source_location()};
2025  }
2026 
2027  // the first parameter must be a function pointer typed assignable path
2028  // expression, without side effects or ternary operator
2029  auto &function_pointer = expr.arguments()[0];
2030 
2031  if(
2032  function_pointer.type().id() != ID_pointer ||
2033  to_pointer_type(function_pointer.type()).base_type().id() != ID_code ||
2034  !function_pointer.get_bool(ID_C_lvalue))
2035  {
2036  throw invalid_source_file_exceptiont(
2037  "the first argument of " CPROVER_PREFIX
2038  "obeys_contract must be a function pointer lvalue expression",
2039  function_pointer.source_location());
2040  }
2041 
2042  if(has_subexpr(function_pointer, ID_if))
2043  {
2044  throw invalid_source_file_exceptiont(
2045  "the first argument of " CPROVER_PREFIX
2046  "obeys_contract must have no ternary operator",
2047  function_pointer.source_location());
2048  }
2049 
2050  // second parameter must be the address of a function symbol
2051  auto &address_of_contract = expr.arguments()[1];
2052 
2053  if(
2054  address_of_contract.id() != ID_address_of ||
2055  to_address_of_expr(address_of_contract).object().id() != ID_symbol ||
2056  address_of_contract.type().id() != ID_pointer ||
2057  to_pointer_type(address_of_contract.type()).base_type().id() != ID_code)
2058  {
2059  throw invalid_source_file_exceptiont(
2060  "the second argument of " CPROVER_PREFIX
2061  "obeys_contract must must be a function symbol",
2062  address_of_contract.source_location());
2063  }
2064 
2065  if(function_pointer.type() != address_of_contract.type())
2066  {
2067  throw invalid_source_file_exceptiont(
2068  "the first and second arguments of " CPROVER_PREFIX
2069  "obeys_contract must have the same function pointer type",
2070  expr.source_location());
2071  }
2072 
2073  expr.type() = bool_typet();
2074 }

2085 void c_typecheck_baset::typecheck_side_effect_function_call(
2086  side_effect_expr_function_callt &expr)
2087 {
2088  if(expr.operands().size()!=2)
2089  {
2090  error().source_location = expr.source_location();
2091  error() << "function_call side effect expects two operands" << eom;
2092  throw 0;
2093  }
2094 
2095  exprt &f_op=expr.function();
2096 
2097  // f_op is not yet typechecked, in contrast to the other arguments.
2098  // This is a big special case!
2099 
2100  if(f_op.id()==ID_symbol)
2101  {
2102  irep_idt identifier=to_symbol_expr(f_op).get_identifier();
2103 
2104  asm_label_mapt::const_iterator entry=
2105  asm_label_map.find(identifier);
2106  if(entry!=asm_label_map.end())
2107  identifier=entry->second;
2108 
2109  if(symbol_table.symbols.find(identifier)==symbol_table.symbols.end())
2110  {
2111  // This is an undeclared function.
2112 
2113  // Is it the polymorphic typed_target function ?
2114  if(identifier == CPROVER_PREFIX "typed_target")
2115  {
2116  typecheck_typed_target_call(expr);
2117  }
2118  // Is this a builtin?
2119  else if(!builtin_factory(identifier))
2120  {
2121  // yes, it's a builtin
2122  }
2123  else if(
2124  identifier == "__noop" &&
2125  config.ansi_c.mode == configt::ansi_ct::flavourt::VISUAL_STUDIO)
2126  {
2127  // https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/cpp/intrinsics/noop
2128  // typecheck and discard, just generating 0 instead
2129  for(auto &op : expr.arguments())
2130  typecheck_expr(op);
2131 
2132  exprt result = from_integer(0, signed_int_type());
2133  expr.swap(result);
2134 
2135  return;
2136  }
2137  else if(
2138  identifier == "__builtin_shuffle" &&
2139  config.ansi_c.mode == configt::ansi_ct::flavourt::GCC)
2140  {
2141  exprt result = typecheck_shuffle_vector(expr);
2142  expr.swap(result);
2143 
2144  return;
2145  }

2147  {
2148  exprt result = typecheck_shuffle_vector(expr);
2149  expr.swap(result);
2150 
2151  return;
2152  }
2153  else if(
2154  identifier == CPROVER_PREFIX "saturating_minus" ||
2155  identifier == CPROVER_PREFIX "saturating_plus")
2156  {
2157  exprt result = typecheck_saturating_arithmetic(expr);
2158  expr.swap(result);
2159 
2160  return;
2161  }
2162  else if(identifier == CPROVER_PREFIX "equal")
2163  {
2164  if(expr.arguments().size() != 2)
2165  {
2166  error().source_location = f_op.source_location();
2167  error() << "equal expects two operands" << eom;
2168  throw 0;
2169  }
2170 
2171  equal_exprt equality_expr(
2172  expr.arguments().front(), expr.arguments().back());
2173  equality_expr.add_source_location() = expr.source_location();
2174 
2175  if(equality_expr.lhs().type() != equality_expr.rhs().type())
2176  {
2177  error().source_location = f_op.source_location();
2178  error() << "equal expects two operands of same type" << eom;
2179  throw 0;
2180  }
2181 
2182  expr.swap(equality_expr);
2183  return;
2184  }
2185  else if(
2186  identifier == CPROVER_PREFIX "overflow_minus" ||
2187  identifier == CPROVER_PREFIX "overflow_mult" ||
2188  identifier == CPROVER_PREFIX "overflow_plus" ||
2189  identifier == CPROVER_PREFIX "overflow_shl")
2190  {
2191  exprt overflow{identifier, typet{}, exprt::operandst{expr.arguments()}};
2192  overflow.add_source_location() = f_op.source_location();
2193 
2194  if(identifier == CPROVER_PREFIX "overflow_minus")
2195  {
2196  overflow.id(ID_minus);
2197  typecheck_expr_binary_arithmetic(overflow);
2198  }
2199  else if(identifier == CPROVER_PREFIX "overflow_mult")
2200  {
2201  overflow.id(ID_mult);
2202  typecheck_expr_binary_arithmetic(overflow);
2203  }
2204  else if(identifier == CPROVER_PREFIX "overflow_plus")
2205  {
2206  overflow.id(ID_plus);
2207  typecheck_expr_binary_arithmetic(overflow);
2208  }
2209  else if(identifier == CPROVER_PREFIX "overflow_shl")
2210  {
2211  overflow.id(ID_shl);
2212  typecheck_expr_shifts(to_shift_expr(overflow));
2213  }

2216  overflow.operands()[0], overflow.id(), overflow.operands()[1]};
2217  of.add_source_location() = overflow.source_location();
2218  expr.swap(of);
2219  return;
2220  }
2221  else if(identifier == CPROVER_PREFIX "overflow_unary_minus")
2222  {

2224  tmp.add_source_location() = f_op.source_location();
2225

2227

2229  overflow.add_source_location() = tmp.source_location();
2230  expr.swap(overflow);
2231  return;
2232  }
2233  else if(identifier == CPROVER_PREFIX "enum_is_in_range")
2234  {
2235  // Check correct number of arguments
2236  if(expr.arguments().size() != 1)
2237  {
2238  std::ostringstream error_message;
2239  error_message << identifier << " takes exactly 1 argument, but "
2240  << expr.arguments().size() << " were provided";
2241  throw invalid_source_file_exceptiont{

2243  }
2244  const auto &arg1 = expr.arguments()[0];
2245  if(!can_cast_type<c_enum_tag_typet>(arg1.type()))
2246  {
2247  // Can't enum range check a non-enum

2249  error_message << identifier << " expects enum, but ("
2250  << expr2c(arg1, *this) << ") has type `"
2251  << type2c(arg1.type(), *this) << '`';
2252  throw invalid_source_file_exceptiont{
2253  error_message.str(), expr.source_location()};

2257  in_range.add_source_location() = expr.source_location();
2258  exprt lowered = in_range.lower(*this);
2259  expr.swap(lowered);
2260  return;
2261  }
2262  else if(
2263  identifier == CPROVER_PREFIX "r_ok" ||
2264  identifier == CPROVER_PREFIX "w_ok" ||
2265  identifier == CPROVER_PREFIX "rw_ok")
2266  {

2268  {

2270  id2string(identifier) + " expects one or two operands",
2271  f_op.source_location()};
2272  }

2275  auto &pointer_expr = expr.arguments()[0];
2276  if(pointer_expr.type().id() == ID_array)
2277  {
2278  auto dest_type = pointer_type(void_type());
2279  dest_type.base_type().set(ID_C_constant, true);
2280  implicit_typecast(pointer_expr, dest_type);
2281  }
2282  else if(pointer_expr.type().id() != ID_pointer)
2283  {
2284  throw invalid_source_file_exceptiont{
2285  id2string(identifier) + " expects a pointer as first argument",
2286  f_op.source_location()};
2287  }
2288

2290  // When not given, use the pointer subtype.
2291  exprt size_expr;
2292 
2293  if(expr.arguments().size() == 2)
2294  {
2295  implicit_typecast(expr.arguments()[1], size_type());
2296  size_expr = expr.arguments()[1];
2297  }
2298  else
2299  {
2300  // Won't do void *
2301  const auto &subtype =
2302  to_pointer_type(pointer_expr.type()).base_type();
2303  if(subtype.id() == ID_empty)
2304  {
2305  throw invalid_source_file_exceptiont{
2306  id2string(identifier) +
2307  " expects a size when given a void pointer",
2308  f_op.source_location()};
2309  }
2310

2312  CHECK_RETURN(size_expr_opt.has_value());
2313  size_expr = std::move(size_expr_opt.value());
2314  }

2317  : identifier == CPROVER_PREFIX "w_ok" ? ID_w_ok
2318  : ID_rw_ok;

2321  ok_expr.add_source_location() = expr.source_location();
2322 
2323  expr.swap(ok_expr);
2324  return;
2325  }

2328  {

2330  shadow_memory_builtin->get_identifier();

2333  to_code_type(shadow_memory_builtin->type());
2334

2341  if(!symbol_table.has_symbol(shadow_memory_builtin_id))

2344  shadow_memory_builtin_id, shadow_memory_builtin->type(), ID_C};
2345  new_symbol.base_name = shadow_memory_builtin_id;
2346  new_symbol.location = f_op.source_location();
2347  // Add an empty implementation to avoid warnings about missing
2348  // implementation later on
2349  new_symbol.value = code_blockt{};
2350

2352  }

2356  f_op = std::move(*shadow_memory_builtin);
2357  }
2358  else if(
2359  auto gcc_polymorphic = typecheck_gcc_polymorphic_builtin(
2360  identifier, expr.arguments(), f_op.source_location()))
2361  {
2362  irep_idt identifier_with_type = gcc_polymorphic->get_identifier();
2363  auto &parameters = to_code_type(gcc_polymorphic->type()).parameters();
2364  INVARIANT(
2365  !parameters.empty(),
2366  "GCC polymorphic built-ins should have at least one parameter");
2367

2369  // by typecheck_gcc_polymorphic_builtin), looking at the first parameter
2370  // suffices to distinguish different implementations.
2371  if(parameters.front().type().id() == ID_pointer)
2372  {
2373  identifier_with_type =
2374  id2string(identifier) + "_" +
2375  type_to_partial_identifier(
2376  to_pointer_type(parameters.front().type()).base_type(), *this);
2377  }
2378  else
2379  {
2380  identifier_with_type =
2381  id2string(identifier) + "_" +
2382  type_to_partial_identifier(parameters.front().type(), *this);
2383  }
2384  gcc_polymorphic->set_identifier(identifier_with_type);
2385 
2386  if(!symbol_table.has_symbol(identifier_with_type))
2387  {
2388  for(std::size_t i = 0; i < parameters.size(); ++i)
2389  {
2390  const std::string base_name = "p_" + std::to_string(i);
2391 
2392  parameter_symbolt new_symbol;
2393 
2394  new_symbol.name =
2395  id2string(identifier_with_type) + "::" + base_name;
2396  new_symbol.base_name = base_name;
2397  new_symbol.location = f_op.source_location();
2398  new_symbol.type = parameters[i].type();
2399  new_symbol.is_parameter = true;
2400  new_symbol.is_lvalue = true;
2401  new_symbol.mode = ID_C;
2402 
2403  parameters[i].set_identifier(new_symbol.name);
2404  parameters[i].set_base_name(new_symbol.base_name);
2405 
2406  symbol_table.add(new_symbol);
2407  }
2408 
2409  symbolt new_symbol{
2410  identifier_with_type, gcc_polymorphic->type(), ID_C};
2411  new_symbol.base_name = identifier_with_type;
2412  new_symbol.location = f_op.source_location();

2414  instantiate_gcc_polymorphic_builtin(identifier, *gcc_polymorphic);
2415  typet parent_return_type = return_type;
2416  return_type = to_code_type(gcc_polymorphic->type()).return_type();
2417  typecheck_code(implementation);
2418  return_type = parent_return_type;
2419  new_symbol.value = implementation;
2420 
2421  symbol_table.add(new_symbol);
2422  }
2423 
2424  f_op = std::move(*gcc_polymorphic);
2425  }
2426  else

2428  // This is an undeclared function that's not a builtin.
2429  // Let's just add it.
2430  // We do a bit of return-type guessing, but just a bit.
2431  typet guessed_return_type = signed_int_type();
2432 
2433  // The following isn't really right and sound, but there
2434  // are too many idiots out there who use malloc and the like
2435  // without the right header file.
2436  if(identifier=="malloc" ||
2437  identifier=="realloc" ||
2438  identifier=="reallocf" ||
2439  identifier=="valloc")
2440  {
2441  guessed_return_type = pointer_type(void_type()); // void *
2442  }
2443

2445  identifier, code_typet({}, guessed_return_type), mode};
2446  new_symbol.base_name=identifier;
2447  new_symbol.location=expr.source_location();
2448  new_symbol.type.set(ID_C_incomplete, true);
2449 
2450  // TODO: should also guess some argument types
2451 
2452  symbolt *symbol_ptr;
2453  move_symbol(new_symbol, symbol_ptr);
2454 
2455  warning().source_location=f_op.find_source_location();
2456  warning() << "function '" << identifier << "' is not declared" << eom;
2457  }
2458  }
2459  }
2460 
2461  // typecheck it now
2462  typecheck_expr(f_op);
2463 
2464  const typet f_op_type = f_op.type();
2465 
2466  if(f_op_type.id() == ID_mathematical_function)
2467  {
2468  const auto &mathematical_function_type =
2469  to_mathematical_function_type(f_op_type);
2470 
2471  // check number of arguments
2472  if(expr.arguments().size() != mathematical_function_type.domain().size())
2473  {
2474  error().source_location = f_op.source_location();
2475  error() << "expected " << mathematical_function_type.domain().size()
2476  << " arguments but got " << expr.arguments().size() << eom;
2477  throw 0;
2478  }
2479 
2480  // check the types of the arguments
2481  for(auto &p :
2482  make_range(expr.arguments()).zip(mathematical_function_type.domain()))
2483  {
2484  if(p.first.type() != p.second)
2485  {
2486  error().source_location = p.first.source_location();
2487  error() << "expected argument of type " << to_string(p.second)
2488  << " but got " << to_string(p.first.type()) << eom;
2489  throw 0;
2490  }
2491  }
2492 
2493  function_application_exprt function_application(f_op, expr.arguments());
2494 
2495  function_application.add_source_location() = expr.source_location();
2496 
2497  expr.swap(function_application);
2498  return;
2499  }
2500 
2501  if(f_op_type.id()!=ID_pointer)
2502  {
2503  error().source_location = f_op.source_location();
2504  error() << "expected function/function pointer as argument but got '"
2505  << to_string(f_op_type) << "'" << eom;
2506  throw 0;
2507  }
2508 
2509  // do implicit dereference
2510  if(f_op.id() == ID_address_of && f_op.get_bool(ID_C_implicit))
2511  {
2512  f_op = to_address_of_expr(f_op).object();
2513  }
2514  else
2515  {
2516  dereference_exprt tmp{f_op};
2517  tmp.set(ID_C_implicit, true);
2518  tmp.add_source_location()=f_op.source_location();
2519  f_op.swap(tmp);
2520  }
2521 
2522  if(f_op.type().id()!=ID_code)
2523  {
2524  error().source_location = f_op.source_location();
2525  error() << "expected code as argument" << eom;
2526  throw 0;
2527  }
2528 
2529  const code_typet &code_type=to_code_type(f_op.type());
2530 
2531  expr.type()=code_type.return_type();
2532 
2533  exprt tmp=do_special_functions(expr);
2534 
2535  if(tmp.is_not_nil())
2536  expr.swap(tmp);
2537  else
2538  typecheck_function_call_arguments(expr);

2541 exprt c_typecheck_baset::do_special_functions(
2542  side_effect_expr_function_callt &expr)
2543 {
2544  const exprt &f_op=expr.function();
2545  const source_locationt &source_location=expr.source_location();
2546 
2547  // some built-in functions
2548  if(f_op.id()!=ID_symbol)
2549  return nil_exprt();
2550 
2551  const irep_idt &identifier=to_symbol_expr(f_op).get_identifier();
2552 
2553  if(identifier == CPROVER_PREFIX "is_fresh")
2554  {
2555  if(expr.arguments().size() != 2)
2556  {
2557  error().source_location = f_op.source_location();
2558  error() << CPROVER_PREFIX "is_fresh expects two operands; "
2559  << expr.arguments().size() << "provided." << eom;
2560  throw 0;
2561  }
2562  typecheck_function_call_arguments(expr);
2563  return nil_exprt();
2564  }
2565  else if(identifier == CPROVER_PREFIX "obeys_contract")
2566  {
2567  typecheck_obeys_contract_call(expr);
2568  // returning nil leaves the call expression in place
2569  return nil_exprt();
2570  }
2571  else if(identifier == CPROVER_PREFIX "pointer_in_range_dfcc")
2572  {
2573  // same as pointer_in_range with experimental support for DFCC contracts
2574  // -- do not use
2575  if(expr.arguments().size() != 3)
2576  {
2577  throw invalid_source_file_exceptiont{
2578  CPROVER_PREFIX "pointer_in_range_dfcc expects three arguments",
2579  expr.source_location()};
2580  }
2581 
2582  for(const auto &arg : expr.arguments())
2583  {
2584  if(arg.type().id() != ID_pointer)
2585  {

3754 
3755 exprt c_typecheck_baset::typecheck_builtin_overflow(
3756  side_effect_expr_function_callt &expr,
3757  const irep_idt &arith_op)
3758 {
3759  const irep_idt &identifier = to_symbol_expr(expr.function()).get_identifier();
3760 
3761  // check function signature
3762  if(expr.arguments().size() != 3)
3763  {
3764  std::ostringstream error_message;
3765  error_message << identifier << " takes exactly 3 arguments, but "
3766  << expr.arguments().size() << " were provided";
3767  throw invalid_source_file_exceptiont{
3768  error_message.str(), expr.source_location()};
3769  }
3770 
3771  typecheck_function_call_arguments(expr);
3772 
3773  auto lhs = expr.arguments()[0];
3774  auto rhs = expr.arguments()[1];
3775  auto result = expr.arguments()[2];
3776 
3777  const bool is__p_variant = has_suffix(id2string(identifier), "_p");
3778 
3779  {
3780  auto const raise_wrong_argument_error =
3781  [this, identifier](
3782  const exprt &wrong_argument, std::size_t argument_number, bool _p) {
3783  std::ostringstream error_message;
3784  error_message << "error: " << identifier << " has signature "
3785  << identifier << "(integral, integral, integral"
3786  << (_p ? "" : "*") << "), "
3787  << "but argument " << argument_number << " ("
3788  << expr2c(wrong_argument, *this) << ") has type `"
3789  << type2c(wrong_argument.type(), *this) << '`';
3790  throw invalid_source_file_exceptiont{
3791  error_message.str(), wrong_argument.source_location()};
3792  };
3793  for(int arg_index = 0; arg_index <= (!is__p_variant ? 1 : 2); ++arg_index)
3794  {
3795  auto const &argument = expr.arguments()[arg_index];
3796 
3797  if(!is_signed_or_unsigned_bitvector(argument.type()))
3798  {
3799  raise_wrong_argument_error(argument, arg_index + 1, is__p_variant);
3800  }
3801  }
3802  if(
3803  !is__p_variant && (result.type().id() != ID_pointer ||
3804  !is_signed_or_unsigned_bitvector(
3805  to_pointer_type(result.type()).base_type())))
3806  {
3807  raise_wrong_argument_error(result, 3, is__p_variant);
3808  }
3809  }
3810 
3811  return side_effect_expr_overflowt{arith_op,
3812  std::move(lhs),
3813  std::move(rhs),
3814  std::move(result),
3815  expr.source_location()};
3816 }
3817 
3818 exprt c_typecheck_baset::typecheck_saturating_arithmetic(
3819  const side_effect_expr_function_callt &expr)
3820 {
3821  const irep_idt &identifier = to_symbol_expr(expr.function()).get_identifier();
3822 
3823  // check function signature
3824  if(expr.arguments().size() != 2)
3825  {
3826  std::ostringstream error_message;
3827  error_message << "error: " << identifier
3828  << " takes exactly two arguments, but "
3829  << expr.arguments().size() << " were provided";
3830  throw invalid_source_file_exceptiont{
3831  error_message.str(), expr.source_location()};
3832  }
3833 
3834  exprt result;
3835  if(identifier == CPROVER_PREFIX "saturating_minus")
3836  result = saturating_minus_exprt{expr.arguments()[0], expr.arguments()[1]};
3837  else if(identifier == CPROVER_PREFIX "saturating_plus")
3838  result = saturating_plus_exprt{expr.arguments()[0], expr.arguments()[1]};
3839  else
3840  UNREACHABLE;
3841 
3842  typecheck_expr_binary_arithmetic(result);
3843  result.add_source_location() = expr.source_location();
3844 
3845  return result;
